@AutografMusic there's two types of authorization, one that is just allowing the site to read your wallet address, then the other which is a lot more important, which is allowing a site to access your tokens. That will always require a full transaction, so just be sure you trust the site there.

@AutografMusic as far as i'm aware, there's no way to fake a signed message without the full wallet being compromised, so it's about as secure as it gets. 

just make sure you have those private keys in a safe place, because your browsers won't save it. somebody i knew lost 3mil+ from a lost pk
